Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.21,0:01:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandpa!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.21,0:01:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandpa, what is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.30,0:01:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did you find this?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.30,0:01:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,In the fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.85,0:01:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Come along.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.85,0:01:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to show you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.90,0:01:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve never told you about my past, have I?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.08,0:01:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Josiah, you are still young now.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.08,0:01:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But one day you’ll learn more about my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.58,0:01:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I did many bad things.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.09,0:01:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to worship false gods instead of Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.05,0:02:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I even brought idols into the temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.14,0:02:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I upset Jehovah very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.28,0:02:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And he disciplined me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.20,0:02:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I begged Jehovah to forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.66,0:02:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he forgive you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.12,0:02:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. His mercy is great!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.88,0:02:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, these are the words of Jehovah’s prophet Isaiah:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.80,0:02:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“All who form carved images
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.05,0:02:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,“amount to nothing,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.22,0:02:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“and their cherished objects will be of no benefit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.19,0:02:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“As their witnesses,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.81,0:02:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“they see nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.98,0:02:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and know nothing.”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.69,0:02:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I want you to read
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.32,0:03:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,these words down here about a man who cuts down a tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.12,0:03:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s see what he does with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.83,0:03:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“Half of it he burns up in a fire;
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.17,0:03:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“with that half
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.92,0:03:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“he roasts the meat that he e-e-eats,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.13,0:03:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“and he is s-s-satisfied.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.26,0:03:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“He also warms himself and says:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.31,0:03:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Ah! I am warm as I watch the fire.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.35,0:03:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that bad, Grandpa?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.60,0:03:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,No, my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.02,0:03:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But let’s see what he does with the other half.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.74,0:03:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“But the rest of it he makes into a god,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.74,0:03:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“into his c-c-carved image.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.62,0:03:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“He bows down to it and worships it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.42,0:03:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“He prays to it and says:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.88,0:03:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Save me, for you are my god.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.05,0:03:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.30,0:04:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it wrong, Josiah?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.89,0:04:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it’s not Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.89,0:04:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s just a tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.18,0:04:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,How does Jehovah feel about doing something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.40,0:04:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah doesn’t want us to serve any other gods?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.48,0:04:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.48,0:04:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, can any other god listen to our prayers?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.16,0:04:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No! Only Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.99,0:04:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jehovah wants to hear your prayers, Josiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.41,0:04:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I always pray to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.50,0:04:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Pray to him many times a day
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.67,0:04:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,from your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.67,0:04:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That shows you love him and want to be his friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.09,0:04:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,If you make a mistake,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.80,0:04:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,pray to Jehovah to forgive you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.14,0:04:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Even for a hundred mistakes?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.23,0:04:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Even for a hundred.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.31,0:04:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,A thousand?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.06,0:04:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.69,0:04:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,A thousand, thousand?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.78,0:05:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Even that many—if you pray to Jehovah to forgive you
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.57,0:05:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and you really keep trying to do what is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.50,0:05:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Josiah, your grandfather needs to rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.02,0:06:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Finish telling me the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.02,0:06:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Where was I?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.69,0:06:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The angel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.69,0:06:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.69,0:06:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Then Jehovah’s angel came down,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.53,0:06:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and whoosh!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.70,0:06:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,he destroyed 185,000 of Sennacherib’s troops.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.16,0:06:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.16,0:06:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.16,0:06:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,King Hezekiah learned
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.17,0:06:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that we can always trust in Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.67,0:06:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I like going to the temple with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.09,0:06:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Zephaniah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.30,0:06:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn’t fill the boy’s head with such stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.72,0:06:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The king told me to take Josiah to the temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.02,0:06:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I know where you’re going, and I don’t care what my father told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.52,0:06:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The boy isn’t—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.52,0:06:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t what?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.15,0:07:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Father, what are you doing out of bed?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.15,0:07:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Josiah wanted to go to the temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.78,0:07:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I had Zephaniah take him along ahead of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.53,0:07:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You may not want to join us,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.45,0:07:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,but you will not prevent Josiah from going.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.55,0:07:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,As you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.31,0:07:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Enan, this is a good one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.20,0:07:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Who should I be this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.57,0:07:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to be King Solomon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.41,0:07:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I was thinking I could be King David.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.73,0:08:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.28,0:08:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring the boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.53,0:08:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,King Manasseh is asking for him!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.36,0:08:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is Josiah?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.41,0:08:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s on his way, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.37,0:08:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandfather!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.41,0:08:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Josiah,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.00,0:08:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.00,0:08:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.09,0:08:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Grandfather, you have to get better.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.51,0:08:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m afraid of being alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.51,0:08:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re not alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.43,0:09:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.44,0:09:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and so is your cousin Zephaniah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.11,0:09:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is holy,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.65,0:09:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and you must serve him
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.36,0:09:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the way he wants us to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.53,0:09:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,—and only that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.75,0:09:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The sacrifices and celebrations at the temple,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.38,0:09:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,they help us be friends with Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.80,0:09:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried to restore pure worship,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.68,0:09:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,but the people still sacrifice on the high places.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.60,0:09:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s temple—we’ve neglected it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.86,0:09:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,How happy the people were when they worshipped
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.12,0:09:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah the right way!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.87,0:10:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s temple and worship
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.37,0:10:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,can be like that again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.17,0:10:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.80,0:10:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Serve Jehovah, Josiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.76,0:10:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,All other gods
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.19,0:10:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,are powerless.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.89,0:11:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m afraid of being alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.15,0:11:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re not alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.99,0:11:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.49,0:12:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,How happy the people were
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.12,0:12:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,when they worshipped Jehovah the right way!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.71,0:12:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s temple
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.55,0:12:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and worship
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.55,0:12:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,can be like that again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.52,0:12:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Josiah!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.08,0:12:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Father, that hurts!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.39,0:13:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,How is business?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.39,0:13:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The Phoenician models are beautiful,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.06,0:13:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and they’re selling briskly, Ben-Mattan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.07,0:13:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Excellent! We’re making a bigger profit on them too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.44,0:13:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,They will bring blessings from Baal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.45,0:13:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I can see the crops flourishing already.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.83,0:13:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah doesn’t like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.75,0:13:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.29,0:13:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We need the help of all the gods,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.59,0:13:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,not just Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.30,0:13:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s not what Grandfather taught me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.34,0:13:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, “All other gods are powerless.”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.05,0:13:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Lower your voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.39,0:13:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Your grandfather knew Topheth better than anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.53,0:14:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You, my son, can become a mighty man with Jehovah’s help
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.11,0:14:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and Baal’s.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.41,0:14:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s not right;
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.33,0:14:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that’s not right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.33,0:14:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If we’re going to worship Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.92,0:14:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,then we need to go to the temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.58,0:14:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandfather said that—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.50,0:14:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind what your grandfather said!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.59,0:14:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s been dead for two years.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.30,0:14:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You are not to speak of him again. Understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.01,0:14:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Zephaniah!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.92,0:14:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Enan, let’s get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.71,0:15:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Enan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.10,0:15:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.56,0:15:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,King Amon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.41,0:15:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Josiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.42,0:15:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.51,0:15:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t make a scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.93,0:15:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,All other gods are powerless!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.43,0:15:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Agh! Let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.90,0:16:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Not here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.36,0:16:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Not standing before Baal!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.07,0:16:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Not—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.26,0:16:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if this year Baal gives us no rain,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.30,0:16:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,we will certainly know why.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.56,0:16:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What the boy did today was blasphemous.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.44,0:16:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you expect?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.07,0:16:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He spent all of his time with my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.44,0:16:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He must be punished!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.78,0:16:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold your tongue if you want to keep it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.41,0:16:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You may be a priest of Baal, but do not forget who’s king here!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.58,0:17:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I most certainly will not.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.34,0:17:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.59,0:17:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Now go!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.59,0:17:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And take that with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.80,0:17:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.72,0:17:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It will remain here for you to reflect upon, my lord the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.58,0:17:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,No! Argh!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.84,0:17:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Help! Help!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.47,0:17:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody has murdered the king!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.08,0:18:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Josiah, you’re not alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.38,0:18:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.63,0:18:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and so is your cousin Zephaniah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.24,0:18:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Long live the king!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.12,0:18:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Long live the king!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.53,0:19:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Long live the king!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.95,0:19:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Long live the king!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.62,0:19:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Long live the king!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.96,0:19:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Long live the king!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.42,0:19:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Long live the king!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.46,0:19:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Long live the king!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.67,0:19:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Long live the king!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.60,0:19:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Enan.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.15,0:19:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.98,0:19:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is a king.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.03,0:19:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Zephaniah,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.99,0:19:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,prophet of Jehovah, so good to see you too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.66,0:19:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,My king,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.66,0:19:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you must feel so overwhelmed by all this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.75,0:19:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I will truly miss your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.54,0:19:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a good, tolerant man
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.88,0:19:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,who allowed everyone to worship as they wished.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.38,0:19:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You know,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.01,0:20:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,your father consulted with me regularly
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.51,0:20:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,on very important matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.31,0:20:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Josiah,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.93,0:20:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,can we still shoot arrows sometimes?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.86,0:20:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.40,0:20:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll leave you, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.44,0:20:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, my sincerest condolences for the loss of your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.33,0:20:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m here
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.70,0:20:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,whenever you need me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.76,0:20:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,OK. Let’s try again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.52,0:20:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep your hand steady—like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.94,0:20:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, don’t focus on the arrow; focus on the target.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.03,0:21:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.83,0:21:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.29,0:21:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ve improved.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.97,0:21:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Enan,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.38,0:21:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d almost given up on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.18,0:21:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re almost done.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.18,0:21:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Enan, let’s see who can hit center first.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.06,0:21:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s no contest.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.27,0:21:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You have more time to practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.02,0:21:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to practice so that I can defeat Jehovah’s enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.19,0:21:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The history of the kings teaches us
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.07,0:21:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,much about good and bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.61,0:21:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,When we carefully study their lives,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.07,0:21:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,we learn that—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.99,0:21:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,—we need to love Jehovah and hate what is bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.20,0:21:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.50,0:21:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But why does it matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.71,0:21:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Weren’t most kings bad anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.12,0:21:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s true, some were.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.67,0:21:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They didn’t trust in Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.38,0:21:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and they didn’t draw close to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.55,0:22:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,When the king does not search for Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.30,0:22:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,everyone suffers, even the good people.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.30,0:22:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,All the more reason to learn from their mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.35,0:22:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you understand what kind of influence a king has?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.40,0:22:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.44,0:22:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,My grandfather was a great man—
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.69,0:22:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,My father says that King Manasseh
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.03,0:22:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,may have been a little brutal,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.66,0:22:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,but he was effective, and he was tolerant.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.20,0:22:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,He gave the people many freedoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.91,0:22:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Enan, having freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.25,0:22:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,means having responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.67,0:22:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The responsibility—
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.46,0:22:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we go again.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.09,0:22:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The responsibility to choose who we will serve
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.55,0:22:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,—Jehovah or other gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.39,0:22:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,My father says that after the Assyrians released Manasseh,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.18,0:22:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,worshipping only one god weakened him
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.85,0:22:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and he started ruling like an old woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.36,0:22:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.07,0:23:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,My grandfather learned the hard way that Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.69,0:23:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is the only true God.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.15,0:23:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And you just insulted him.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.15,0:23:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,My father simply sees the mistakes your grandfather made.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.57,0:23:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Your father should keep his views to himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.91,0:23:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.41,0:23:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Your father trusted him,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.87,0:23:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and you should too.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.33,0:23:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, you can be loyal to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.79,0:23:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and to Baal, Malcam, or any other god at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.92,0:23:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You don’t honestly believe that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.55,0:23:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.59,0:23:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Your father keeps confusing people.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.14,0:23:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So are you telling me I should disrespect him?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.97,0:23:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the proverb that says:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.43,0:23:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“Listen to your father who caused your birth”?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.85,0:23:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Enan, we must respect our parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.90,0:23:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But all of us, including our parents,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.32,0:23:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,owe our lives to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.32,0:23:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,If we just go along with our parents
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.32,0:23:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in doing something Jehovah hates,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.24,0:23:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,aren’t we honoring them more than Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.54,0:23:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,He just makes me so mad!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.58,0:24:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“My grandfather was a great man, and you insult him.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.38,0:24:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Zephaniah is a prophet; you must listen to him!”
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.84,0:24:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Prophets come and go.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.55,0:24:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s not even old enough to be a real prophet.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.93,0:24:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What is he—25 at the most?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.06,0:24:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And why do we only need to worship Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.31,0:24:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,People worship lots of gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.86,0:24:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Be careful what you say around Josiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.57,0:24:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,His over-righteous spirit may one day turn dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.90,0:24:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to help him be more
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.97,0:24:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,balanced, reasonable.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.41,0:24:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.58,0:24:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Zephaniah says he has a spirit like David.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.83,0:24:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfaithful David,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.84,0:24:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,who stole another man’s wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.55,0:24:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.52,0:24:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Talk to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.74,0:25:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What if Josiah is right?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.15,0:25:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Right about what?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.41,0:25:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What if there really is only one true God?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.08,0:25:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Son, Josiah doesn’t see the bigger picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.42,0:25:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,His-his grandfather did before he weakened.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.80,0:25:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What can I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.51,0:25:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Talk to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.68,0:25:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Help him to be a good king
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.35,0:25:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,—tolerant—
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.02,0:25:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,like Manasseh was.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.07,0:25:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s what you can tell him.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.99,0:25:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Josiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.33,0:26:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted—
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.00,0:26:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.38,0:26:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I shouldn’t have spoken to you like that yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.17,0:26:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.38,0:26:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgave you already.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.68,0:26:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t want any problems between us.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.01,0:26:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s just,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.26,0:26:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,what if you’re wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.56,0:26:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What if Baal worship is important?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.52,0:26:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.77,0:26:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Baal is the god of the life-giving rains,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.77,0:26:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and your father and grandfather sacrificed on the high places.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.74,0:26:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But what if Baal cuts off the rains
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.70,0:26:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,because you don’t?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.91,0:26:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The crops would die, and the people would starve,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.12,0:26:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and then they would revolt against you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.54,0:26:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I know how you feel about Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.72,0:26:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But isn’t it better to offer the other sacrifices too
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.55,0:27:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,—just in case?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.48,0:27:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would I worry about that when it’s only Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.31,0:27:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,who can control the weather,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.15,0:27:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,not some false rain god?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.41,0:27:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t you remember,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.41,0:27:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,King Solomon wrote: “All the streams”—
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.50,0:27:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.71,0:27:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,“All the streams flow into the sea, yet the sea is not full.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.55,0:27:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“To the place from which the streams flow,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.01,0:27:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,there they return so as to flow again.”
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.72,0:27:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s right,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.10,0:27:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,just as Jehovah designed.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.10,0:27:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We studied that scroll together.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.60,0:27:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, some people say the scrolls have been altered.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.69,0:27:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe the gods are trying to tell us that—
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.69,0:27:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember when we were little,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.32,0:27:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,we would play in the fields?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.32,0:28:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.83,0:28:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You always wanted to be King Solomon.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.08,0:28:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah gave Solomon wisdom and riches,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.92,0:28:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,but do you also remember the end of the story?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.21,0:28:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,His wives inclined his heart to follow other gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.72,0:28:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,His heart wasn’t complete with Jehovah like David’s was.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.35,0:28:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t want to make that same mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.41,0:28:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you drawing?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.24,0:28:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s the temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.41,0:28:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,My grandfather told me how beautiful the temple was
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.08,0:28:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,when people would worship Jehovah properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.42,0:28:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He said it could be that way again.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.60,0:29:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll tell you what I intend to do as king.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.68,0:29:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You don’t understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.77,0:29:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Josiah plans to tear down all the high places!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.69,0:29:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I understand all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.99,0:29:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,When his extremist ideas
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.99,0:29:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,become the law of the land,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.66,0:29:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,there will no longer be any joy,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.95,0:29:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,no tolerance, no freedom of worship
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.25,0:29:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,—only narrow-minded rules
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.42,0:29:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and oppressed people.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.26,0:29:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you understand that?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.68,0:29:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not a good sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.46,0:30:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is holy,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.01,0:30:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and you must serve him the way he wants us to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.68,0:30:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,—and only that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.81,0:30:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You, my son,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.23,0:30:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,can become a mighty man
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.53,0:30:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,with Jehovah’s help
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.49,0:30:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and Baal’s.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.99,0:30:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,When the king does not search for Jehovah, everyone suffers,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.87,0:30:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,even the good people.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.62,0:30:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What if you’re wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.09,0:31:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t it better to offer the other sacrifices too
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.84,0:31:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,—just in case?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.81,0:31:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Serve Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.90,0:31:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Josiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.19,0:31:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,All other gods
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.65,0:31:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,are powerless.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.00,0:31:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,O Jehovah!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.83,0:01:05.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,おじいちゃん
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.34,0:01:08.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,おじいちゃん これ何？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.84,0:01:14.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,どこにあった？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.76,0:01:16.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこの原っぱ
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.43,0:01:21.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうか
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.19,0:01:23.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,教えてあげよう おいで
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.27,0:01:28.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,おじいちゃんの若いころの話\Nまだしてなかったね
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.12,0:01:40.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨシヤ お前はまだ子供だから
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.00,0:01:44.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,おじいちゃんのことを\Nそんなによく知らないが
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.46,0:01:49.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,おじいちゃんは悪いことを\Nたくさんしたんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.17,0:01:56.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバではなく 偽りの\N神々を崇拝していた
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.05,0:02:02.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,偶像を エホバの神殿に\N持ち込むことさえしたんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.73,0:02:06.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで エホバはとてもお怒りになった
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.44,0:02:14.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,私はエホバから厳しく\N正されなければならなかった
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.32,0:02:20.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,許してくださいとエホバに\N心からお願いした
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.74,0:02:22.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,許してもらえたの？
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.04,0:02:27.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうだ エホバは本当に\N憐れみ深い方だ！
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.96,0:02:32.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの預言者イザヤの言葉がある
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.76,0:02:34.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここだ
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.43,0:02:39.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,「彫刻像を作る者は皆むなしく
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.60,0:02:44.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼らがあがめている物は\N何の役にも立たない
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.27,0:02:47.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,それらの像は何も見ず
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.69,0:02:50.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,何も知らないので
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.61,0:02:53.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,証人にはなり得ない」
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.94,0:02:57.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨシヤ お前にも読んで欲しいんだが
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.57,0:03:00.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,木を切り倒した人の話だ
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.20,0:03:02.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,その木で何をするかな？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.00,0:03:08.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,「木の 半分を 火の中で… 燃やす
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.33,0:03:12.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで 肉をあぶり
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.92,0:03:16.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,食べて… 満足する
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.55,0:03:21.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,また 暖を 取って… こう言う
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.35,0:03:25.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,『ああ 火を見ていたら… 温まった』」
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.56,0:03:27.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,これって 良くないことなの？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.94,0:03:32.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,いいや でも 残りの半分で\N何をするか読んでごらん
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.03,0:03:39.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,「残りの木で 彫刻像を作り
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.32,0:03:43.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の神とする
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.00,0:03:50.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,それに ひれ伏し 崇拝し
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.42,0:03:54.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,それに向かって 祈ってこう言う
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.09,0:03:58.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,『救ってください\Nあなたは私の神です』」
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.26,0:03:59.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,これはだめ！
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.89,0:04:03.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨシヤ どうしてだめだと思う？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.39,0:04:06.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバじゃないもん ただの木だもん
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.31,0:04:10.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,これを見て エホバはどう思うかな？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.48,0:04:14.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほかの神に祈ったら エホバ嫌でしょ？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.48,0:04:16.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうだね
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.24,0:04:20.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,それに ほかの神は祈りを聞けるかな？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.20,0:04:22.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,聞けない！ 聞けるのはエホバだけ
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.95,0:04:27.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,そしてエホバは お前の祈りを\N聞きたがっておられる
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.50,0:04:29.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつもエホバに祈ってる
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.50,0:04:33.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,1日に何度も祈りなさい
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.67,0:04:36.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうするなら お前がエホバを愛し
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.96,0:04:40.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,友だちになりたいということを伝えられる
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.76,0:04:43.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,もし 間違ったことをしてしまったなら
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.85,0:04:46.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,許しを求めなさい
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.39,0:04:49.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,100回間違えても？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.31,0:04:51.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうだ 100回でも
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.73,0:04:53.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,1000回でも？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.06,0:04:54.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうだよ
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.94,0:04:57.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,100万回でも？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.07,0:04:58.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,いくらでも…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.86,0:05:01.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,お前がエホバの許しを求めて祈り
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.95,0:05:06.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当に正しいことを行おうと\N努力し続けるなら…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.42,0:05:20.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨシヤ おじいちゃんは\Nちょっと休憩だ
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.52,0:06:13.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,つづきを教えてよ
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.39,0:06:14.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,どこからだっけ？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.77,0:06:16.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,天使がどうしたの？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.77,0:06:18.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうだったね
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.15,0:06:21.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,するとその時
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.07,0:06:25.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの天使がやってきて\Nシュー！
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.74,0:06:32.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,18万5000人もいたセナケリブの\N軍隊を全部滅ぼしたんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.16,0:06:33.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,すごいね
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.29,0:06:36.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,そう！ それでヒゼキヤ王は
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.17,0:06:39.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつもエホバに頼ることの\N大切さを学んだんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.13,0:06:41.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,ゼパニヤの話 楽しい
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.13,0:06:42.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,はは
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.38,0:06:44.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,ゼパニヤ！
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.47,0:06:50.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,そういう話はしないでくれ
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.68,0:06:52.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨシヤを神殿に連れて\N行くよう 王から…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.68,0:06:56.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,分かってる でも親父の言うこと\Nなんか聞くな ヨシヤは…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.06,0:06:58.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうした？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.81,0:07:00.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,父さん 寝てなくていいんですか？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.86,0:07:03.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨシヤは神殿に行きたがっている
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.36,0:07:07.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,だから 私はゼパニヤに頼んだんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.16,0:07:11.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,お前はそれを望まないかもしれないが
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.66,0:07:15.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨシヤが神殿に行くのを\N止めることはできない
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.63,0:07:24.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうぞご自由に
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.77,0:07:42.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,エナン これでいいかな
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.45,0:07:49.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,今日はだれになる？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.70,0:07:52.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,ぼくはソロモン
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.28,0:07:55.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,ぼくはダビデ王になりたいな
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.86,0:08:24.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,急いでください！
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.78,0:08:28.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,マナセ王がヨシヤをお呼びです！
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.28,0:08:31.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨシヤはどこだ
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.45,0:08:33.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,もうすぐ 来られます
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.95,0:08:38.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,おじいちゃん！
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.21,0:08:41.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨシヤ
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.88,0:08:44.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,よく来てくれた
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.21,0:08:47.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,話したいことがある
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.63,0:08:53.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,おじいちゃん 元気になって\Nぼくを一人にしないで
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.39,0:08:56.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,お前は一人じゃない
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.56,0:09:01.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが一緒にいてくださる
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.94,0:09:04.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,いとこのゼパニヤもいる
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.65,0:09:09.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは聖なる方で
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.40,0:09:17.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,お前はエホバが望まれる仕方で\Nただエホバだけに仕えなければならない
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.41,0:09:19.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,分かるだろ
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.08,0:09:21.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,神殿で犠牲を捧げたり
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.08,0:09:24.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,儀式を行ったりするのは
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.00,0:09:29.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバと親しく 友のように\Nなるためのものだ
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.05,0:09:33.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,私は 清い崇拝を取り戻そうとしたが
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.68,0:09:38.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,人々は今でも
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.02,0:09:42.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,高い場所で犠牲を捧げている
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.81,0:09:46.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの神殿
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.15,0:09:51.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,我々はそれを大切にしてこなかった
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.15,0:09:56.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,正しい仕方でエホバを崇拝していた時は
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.45,0:09:59.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,みんな幸せだった
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.58,0:10:03.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの神殿と崇拝は
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.33,0:10:06.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,再びそのようになるはずだ
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.72,0:10:15.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,いいかい ヨシヤ
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.47,0:10:19.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバにお仕えするんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.10,0:10:25.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほかの神には何の力もない
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.89,0:11:00.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,ぼくを一人にしないで
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.27,0:11:11.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,お前は一人じゃない
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.07,0:11:18.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが一緒にいてくださる
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.70,0:12:08.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,正しい仕方でエホバを崇拝していた時は
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.21,0:12:11.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,みんな幸せだった
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.17,0:12:18.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの神殿と崇拝は
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.13,0:12:21.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,再びそのようになるはずだ
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.69,0:12:33.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨシヤ！
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.96,0:12:51.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,お父さん 痛いよ！
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.43,0:13:10.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,商売はどうだ？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.94,0:13:12.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,フェニキアのはきれいだから
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.73,0:13:15.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,おかげでよく売れてるわ ベン・マタン
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.27,0:13:17.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,いいことだ！ みんなが像を欲しがり
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.98,0:13:20.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,我々も豊かになる
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.07,0:13:22.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,バアル様の祝福だ
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.03,0:13:27.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,今年も豊作にしてくださった
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.91,0:13:30.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは像が嫌いだ
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.71,0:13:32.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,やめなさい！
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.59,0:13:40.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバだけじゃなく 全ての\N神の助けが必要なんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.26,0:13:43.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,おじいちゃんはそんなこと言わなかった
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.05,0:13:46.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほかの神には何の力もない
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.10,0:13:48.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,静かにしなさい
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.52,0:13:52.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,お前のおじいちゃんもトフェトで\N犠牲を捧げていたんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.53,0:14:02.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨシヤ お前が強い男になるには
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.65,0:14:06.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバとバアルの助けが必要だ
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.66,0:14:08.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,そんなのうそだ…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.79,0:14:11.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,絶対違う
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.21,0:14:16.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを崇拝したいなら 神殿に\N行きなさいって おじいちゃんは言った
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.63,0:14:19.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,もう忘れるんだ！
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.84,0:14:23.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,死んでもう2年になるんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.68,0:14:27.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,おじいちゃんのことは\N二度と言うな 分かったな
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.89,0:14:31.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,ゼパニヤ！
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.88,0:14:59.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,エナン ここから出よう
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.09,0:15:04.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,エナン
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.22,0:15:13.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,だめ！
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.89,0:15:15.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,アモン王
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.62,0:15:32.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨシヤ
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.84,0:15:48.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨシヤ 恥をかかせるな
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.38,0:15:51.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほかの神には何の力もない！
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.60,0:15:58.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,わー！ やめて！ いやだ！ 放して！
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.98,0:16:00.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,言うことを聞け！
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.56,0:16:02.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,バアルの前にいるんだぞ！
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.40,0:16:05.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,ああっ！
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.09,0:16:26.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,あー
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.55,0:16:30.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,今年バアルが雨を降らせて\Nくださらないとすれば
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.76,0:16:34.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,その理由ははっきりしています
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.68,0:16:39.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,今日あの子がやったことは明らかに
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.31,0:16:41.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,冒とくです
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.69,0:16:44.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,仕方ないだろ
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.86,0:16:48.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,あの子は私の父とずっと一緒にいたんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.78,0:16:51.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,あの子を罰するべきです！
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.07,0:16:53.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,調子に乗るんじゃない！
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.33,0:16:59.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,お前はバアルの祭司かもしれないが\Nこの国の王は私だ！
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.04,0:17:03.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは失礼いたしました
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.96,0:17:07.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,いいだろう 下がれ！
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.21,0:17:10.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,それも持って行け
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.93,0:17:12.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,いや
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.97,0:17:17.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,これはあなたの責任ですから わが主よ
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.70,0:17:39.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,何だ！ やめろ！ うわー！
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.13,0:17:54.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,大変だ！ だれか！ 王が殺された！
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.88,0:18:27.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨシヤ
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.04,0:18:30.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,お前は一人じゃない
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.42,0:18:34.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが一緒にいてくださる
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.18,0:18:39.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,いとこのゼパニヤもいる
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.15,0:18:57.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,王が栄えますように！
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.20,0:18:59.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,王が栄えますように！
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.58,0:19:02.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,王が栄えますように！
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.16,0:19:04.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,王が栄えますように！
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.75,0:19:07.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,王が栄えますように！
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.08,0:19:09.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,王が栄えますように！
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.42,0:19:11.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,王が栄えますように！
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.92,0:19:14.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,王が栄えますように！
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.51,0:19:16.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,王が栄えますように！
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.81,0:19:27.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,エナン
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.56,0:19:31.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨシヤ王 わが主よ
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.32,0:19:38.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,これはこれはエホバの預言者ゼパニヤ様
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.66,0:19:41.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,王よ お気持ち お察しいたします
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.62,0:19:44.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,お父様がおられなくなって
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.75,0:19:47.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,私も本当に寂しいです
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.83,0:19:49.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,あの方はおおらかで
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.88,0:19:53.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,自由な礼拝をお許しくださいました
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.88,0:19:57.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,そしてご存じでしょうが
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.59,0:20:03.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,お父様は大切なことは いつもこの私に\N相談してくださっていました
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.47,0:20:06.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨシヤ
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.14,0:20:10.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,また一緒に弓のけいこできる？
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.69,0:20:12.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうだね
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.19,0:20:16.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,では今日はこの辺で
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.86,0:20:20.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,お父様のことは本当にお気の毒でした
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.28,0:20:24.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,わが主よ いつでも遠慮なく\Nお呼びください
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.91,0:20:26.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,いいですね
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.89,0:20:45.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,よし もう1回やろう
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.52,0:20:55.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,しっかり腕を固定して… いい
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.03,0:20:58.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,矢を見るんじゃなくて
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.07,0:21:00.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,的をよく見るんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.70,0:21:03.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,こんな感じ？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.78,0:21:05.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうだね
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.38,0:21:17.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,上達したね
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.38,0:21:23.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,エナン 来ないと思ってたよ
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.59,0:21:25.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,終わるところだ
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.26,0:21:28.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,エナン 勝負しようか
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.31,0:21:31.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,やだよ 勝てるわけないし
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.19,0:21:35.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,練習しなきゃ エホバの敵を倒すために
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.86,0:21:42.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,王たちの歴史から良いことと\N悪いことについて多くを学べるんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.07,0:21:43.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,だからよく調べるならそのことが…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.91,0:21:48.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,「…エホバを愛し 悪を憎め」ですよね
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.16,0:21:52.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,分かってますよ でも ほとんどの\N王は悪かったんでしょう？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.37,0:21:54.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,確かにそうだね
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.71,0:21:59.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼らはエホバを信頼しなかったし\N近づこうともしなかった
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.88,0:22:02.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,王がエホバを求めないなら
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.30,0:22:04.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,みんなが苦しむことになる
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.47,0:22:08.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,だから 王たちの失敗から\N学ぶべきなんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.64,0:22:15.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,王の影響力は本当に大きいね
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.40,0:22:19.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうですね
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.82,0:22:21.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,祖父はとても立派でした
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.44,0:22:25.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,うちの親父に言わせると\Nマナセ王は残忍だったらしいよ
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.66,0:22:28.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも おおらかで 寛大で
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.62,0:22:30.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,民を自由にさせてたって
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.83,0:22:36.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,エナン 自由には責任が伴うんだ\Nそして 責任というものは…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.17,0:22:38.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,また始まった
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.50,0:22:42.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちには どの神に仕えるかを\N選ぶ責任がある
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.84,0:22:45.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバかほかの神か
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.39,0:22:47.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,親父が言うには
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.93,0:22:51.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,マナセがアッシリアから\N釈放されてからというもの
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.64,0:22:54.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバだけを崇拝するようになって
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.14,0:22:57.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,その支配も腰抜けになったんだって
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.40,0:23:03.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,違う 祖父はエホバだけが本当の\N神だと学んだんだ 侮辱するな
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.57,0:23:07.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,親父は 自分の目で\N見てきたことを言ってるんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.32,0:23:09.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,君のお父さんは 間違ってる
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.08,0:23:11.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,何言ってるんだ 君の父さんみたいに
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.79,0:23:15.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,君もうちの親父を信頼したらいいよ
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.04,0:23:17.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうすれば エホバにも
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.29,0:23:20.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,バアルにも上手に従うことができるさ
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.34,0:23:22.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほんとにそう思ってるのか？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.76,0:23:25.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,ああ もちろん
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.72,0:23:29.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,君の父さんはみんなを惑わしてる
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.89,0:23:33.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,だったら親に逆らえとでも言うのか？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.31,0:23:34.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,格言にこうあるぞ
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.98,0:23:38.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,「あなたを誕生させた\N父親の言うことを聞け」
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.27,0:23:41.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,もちろん親に敬意を払うべきだ
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.15,0:23:45.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 親も含めてみんなが\Nエホバから命をいただいている
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.36,0:23:49.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,もし親と一緒にエホバの\N憎まれることをするなら
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.78,0:23:54.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバより自分の親を高めて\Nいることになるんじゃないかな
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.75,0:23:59.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当に頭にくるよ！
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.21,0:24:01.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,「私の祖父は立派だった
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.46,0:24:03.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,侮辱するんじゃない
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.84,0:24:06.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,預言者ゼパニヤの\N言うことを聞くべきだ！」
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.72,0:24:08.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,預言者だと
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.43,0:24:11.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,話にならん
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.80,0:24:14.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,あいつはまだ若すぎる
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.22,0:24:16.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,今いくつだ？ せいぜい25だ…
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.02,0:24:21.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもどうして 神々じゃなくて\Nエホバだけを崇拝すべきなの？
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.11,0:24:24.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨシヤの前では言葉に気を付けるんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.28,0:24:27.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,あいつの行き過ぎた正義感は危険だ
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.11,0:24:29.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,何をしでかすか分からん
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.45,0:24:33.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,あいつが物分かりの良い\N人間になれるよう助けてやれ
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.33,0:24:35.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうやって！
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.08,0:24:38.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,ゼパニヤは ヨシヤが\Nダビデに似てるって
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.12,0:24:40.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,はっはっはっ！
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.33,0:24:46.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,他人の妻を奪った 不忠実なダビデ
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.80,0:24:53.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうした？
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.60,0:25:00.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,言いたいことがあるのか
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.36,0:25:09.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨシヤが正しいとしたら？
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.03,0:25:12.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,どういう意味だ？
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.37,0:25:16.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,神がただひとりだとしたら
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.91,0:25:20.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,エナン
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.00,0:25:24.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨシヤの見方は狭すぎるんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.17,0:25:28.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,あいつのじいさんは良かった
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.80,0:25:31.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,腰抜けになる前は…
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.68,0:25:34.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうしたらいいの？
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.39,0:25:37.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,あいつと話をしろ
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.72,0:25:40.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,物分かりのいい王になれるよう
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.98,0:25:43.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,助けてやるんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.06,0:25:45.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,マナセのようにな
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.36,0:25:48.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,こんなふうに言えばいい…
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.16,0:25:57.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨシヤ
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.70,0:26:02.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,ちょっと謝りたい
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.00,0:26:06.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,昨日は
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.17,0:26:08.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,あんな言い方をすべきじゃなかった
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.30,0:26:11.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,大丈夫 もう忘れたよ
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.97,0:26:14.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,ただ もう少し話したいことがあるんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.39,0:26:17.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,要するに もし君が\N間違っているとすれば…
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.43,0:26:22.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,そしてもし バアル崇拝が\N必要だとすれば…
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.44,0:26:26.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,考えてくれ バアルは\N命をもたらす雨の神だ
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.02,0:26:29.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,君のお父さんやおじいさんも
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.11,0:26:31.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,高い場所で犠牲をささげた
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.49,0:26:36.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,でももし 君がバアルを\N崇拝しないために
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.45,0:26:39.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,雨が降らないとすれば…
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.00,0:26:44.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,作物はだめになり 人々は飢えてしまう
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.21,0:26:47.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうなったら 人々は\N君に反抗するだろう
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.59,0:26:52.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに対する君の気持ちは分かる
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.67,0:26:56.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 念のために
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.14,0:27:00.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,別の神にも犠牲をささげた方が\N良いんじゃないかな
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.60,0:27:06.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,そんなこと心配しなくていい
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.90,0:27:10.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,天気をコントロールできるのは\Nエホバだけだ
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.87,0:27:21.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,覚えてるだろう
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.95,0:27:24.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,ソロモン王が書いたこと\N 「川は海に流れていく…」
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.50,0:27:26.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,ああ覚えてるよ
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.04,0:27:30.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,「川は 海に流れていく
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.34,0:27:36.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし 海があふれることはない
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.80,0:27:40.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,川は 始まりから また流れる」
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.01,0:27:44.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの設計どおりだ
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.10,0:27:47.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,巻物 勉強したよね
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.19,0:27:51.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,だけど 巻物は書き変えられた\Nと言う人もいる
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.73,0:27:54.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,神々はそれを教えようと\Nしてるんじゃないかな
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.78,0:27:56.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,子供のころ
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.95,0:27:59.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,一緒に遊んだの覚えてる？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.37,0:28:02.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,もちろん
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.08,0:28:05.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,君はいつもソロモン王を\Nやりたがってたね
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.00,0:28:09.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,確かにエホバはソロモンに\N知恵と富を与えたけど
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.96,0:28:12.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,最後にどうなったか覚えてるだろ？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.67,0:28:17.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,大勢の妻たちは ソロモンの心を\Nほかの神々に向けさせた
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.09,0:28:21.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼の心はエホバに対してダビデように\Nひたむきではなかった
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.68,0:28:26.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,ぼくはソロモンと同じ失敗はしたくない
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.66,0:28:43.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,何描いてるの？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.49,0:28:46.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,神殿だよ
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.62,0:28:49.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,祖父は エホバを正しく崇拝した時
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.33,0:28:52.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,神殿は美しかったと言っていた
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.50,0:28:57.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,また必ずそうなる
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.85,0:29:07.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,ぼくの計画を言っておくよ
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.52,0:29:10.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,父さんは分かってない！
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.85,0:29:13.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨシヤは高い場所を取り壊すつもりだ！
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.78,0:29:19.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,ああ よく分かってるよ
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.90,0:29:25.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,あいつがその過激な考えを\N行動に移してしまったら
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.74,0:29:30.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,もうそこには喜びも 寛容さも
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.87,0:29:33.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰の自由も無くなってしまう
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.88,0:29:37.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,残るものといえば ただ狭量な支配と
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.88,0:29:40.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,圧政に苦しむ人々だけだ
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.42,0:29:43.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,お前そこ分かってるのか？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.89,0:29:47.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは良くない兆しだ
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.79,0:30:15.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,ただエホバだけに仕えなければならない
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.04,0:30:19.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは聖なる方で
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.89,0:30:28.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,お前はエホバが望まれる仕方で
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.35,0:30:32.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,ただエホバだけに仕えなければならない
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.73,0:30:34.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,分かるだろ
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.14,0:30:35.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,お父さん 痛いよ！
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.40,0:30:38.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨシヤ お前が強い男になるには
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.23,0:30:43.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバとバアルの助けが必要だ
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.12,0:30:48.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,王がエホバを求めないなら
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.28,0:30:51.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,みんなが苦しむことになる
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.79,0:30:59.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,もし君が間違えているとすれば…
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.84,0:31:05.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,念のために 別の神にも犠牲を\Nささげた方が良いんじゃないかな
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.27,0:31:15.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨシヤ エホバにお仕えするんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.19,0:31:20.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバにお仕えするんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.15,0:31:25.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほかの神には
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.95,0:31:28.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,何の力もない
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.25,0:31:48.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバよ！
